Package: semdistflow
Type: Package
Title: semdistflow: semantic distance for natural language samples
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jamie", "Reilly", role = c("aut", "cre"), email ="jamie_reilly@temple.edu"),
    person(c("Bonnie",  "M."), "Zuckerman", role = c("aut")), 
    person(c("Celia", "P."), "Litovsky", role = c("ctb")),
    person("Ann Marie ", "Finley", role = c("ctb")))
Maintainer: Jamie Reilly <jamie_reilly@temple.edu>
Description: Options for reading natural language text into R, cleaning and stripping the text to isolate open class words, tokenizing into sequential bigrams and computing two metrics of cosine semantic distance for each running bigram.
